We're looking for a Data Scientist to join KWAN on a project where data meets real-world scale helping our client transform rich, cross-industry data into intelligent products and services. This is a Hybrid challenge with 2 office days based in Porto or Lisbon, Portugal.




🛠 The Challenge:

Analyze and interpret large, complex datasets to generate actionable business insights; Build, deploy, and monitor machine learning models that support strategic initiatives and drive performance;
Collaborate with data engineers to ensure reliable, accessible, and well-structured data for model development;
Translate business needs into analytical questions and communicate results clearly to non-technical stakeholders;
Design and implement feature engineering strategies to enhance model effectiveness; Develop and maintain pipelines for model training and evaluation;
Promote best practices in MLOps/LLMOps, ensuring scalability and performance in production;
Foster a data-first mindset across teams, encouraging statistical thinking and experimentation.




🔎 What you bring to the table:

Bachelor's or Master's degree in Mathematics, Statistics, Computer Science, Engineering, or a related technical field;
3+ years of solid experience developing, validating, and deploying ML models end-to-end; Hands-on experience with feature engineering, model tuning, and lifecycle management;
Ability to bridge the gap between business problems and data solutions with clarity and precision;
Proficiency in Python and SQL, with familiarity with cloud-based data platforms such as AWS, Azure, or GCP;
Confidence managing complexity and ambiguity with autonomy;
Strong interpersonal skills and comfort communicating with non-technical audiences;
Curiosity, creativity, and a genuine drive to keep learning.
Solid English proficiency (B2+).




